1511. Customer Order Frequency
68.6%
简单
Write an SQL query to report the customer_id and customer_name of customers who have spent at least $100 in each month of June and July 2020.

Return the result table in any order.

The query result format is in the following example.

 
Example 1:

Input: 
Customers table:
+--------------+-----------+-------------+
| customer_id  | name      | country     |
+--------------+-----------+-------------+
| 1            | Winston   | USA         |
| 2            | Jonathan  | Peru        |
| 3            | Moustafa  | Egypt       |
+--------------+-----------+-------------+
Product table:
+--------------+-------------+-------------+
| product_id   | description | price       |
+--------------+-------------+-------------+
| 10           | LC Phone    | 300         |
| 20           | LC T-Shirt  | 10          |
| 30           | LC Book     | 45          |
| 40           | LC Keychain | 2           |
+--------------+-------------+-------------+
Orders table:
+--------------+-------------+-------------+-------------+-----------+
| order_id     | customer_id | product_id  | order_date  | quantity  |
+--------------+-------------+-------------+-------------+-----------+
| 1            | 1           | 10          | 2020-06-10  | 1         |
| 2            | 1           | 20          | 2020-07-01  | 1         |
| 3            | 1           | 30          | 2020-07-08  | 2         |
| 4            | 2           | 10          | 2020-06-15  | 2         |
| 5            | 2           | 40          | 2020-07-01  | 10        |
| 6            | 3           | 20          | 2020-06-24  | 2         |
| 7            | 3           | 30          | 2020-06-25  | 2         |
| 9            | 3           | 30          | 2020-05-08  | 3         |
+--------------+-------------+-------------+-------------+-----------+
Output: 
+--------------+------------+
| customer_id  | name       |  
+--------------+------------+
| 1            | Winston    |
+--------------+------------+
Explanation: 
Winston spent $300 (300 * 1) in June and $100 ( 10 * 1 + 45 * 2) in July 2020.
Jonathan spent $600 (300 * 2) in June and $20 ( 2 * 10) in July 2020.
Moustafa spent $110 (10 * 2 + 45 * 2) in June and $0 in July 2020.

# Write your MySQL query statement below
 
-- $100 in each month of June and July 2020.
 
SELECT o.customer_id, c.name
FROM Customers c, Products p, Orders o
WHERE c.ustomer_id = o.customer_id
AND p.product_id  = o.product_id 
AND order_date  BETWEEN '2020-06-01' AND '2020-07-31'
GROUP BY o.customer_id  -- 要記得分組！！！
HAVING SUM(IF(MONTH(order_date) = 6, p.price*o.quantity,0)) >=100
AND SUM(IF(MONTH(order_date) = 7, p.price*o.quantity,0)) >=100
